# Statistical Research Orchestration

## When to run FULL 10-phase pipeline:

- New signal type never validated before
- Signal intended for autonomous execution (no human in loop)
- Signal with asymmetric cost (false positive expensive)
- Signal being promoted from research to production

## When to run QUICK checks (phases 1-4 only):

- Iterating on existing, already-validated signal
- Exploratory analysis
- Feature engineering for existing model

## When to SKIP this skill entirely:

- Simple descriptive statistics (mean, median, count)
- Logging, monitoring, or visualization tasks
- Data cleaning without predictive claims
